---
import Container from "@components/container.astro";
import { Picture } from "astro:assets";
const { entry } = Astro.props;
import RelatedArticles from "@components/related-articles.astro";
import JsonLd from "@components/JsonLd.astro";
import Cta from "./cta.astro";

const jsonLdData = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Article",
  headline: `Best Self Hosted ${entry.data.title} Alternative`,
  datePublished: entry.data.publishDate.toISOString(),
  author: {
    "@type": "Person",
    name: entry.data.author,
  },
  keywords: entry.data.tags.join(", "),
  image: entry.data.image.src,
  description: entry.data.description,
};
---

<Container>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl text-center mt-14">
    <h1
      class="text-3xl lg:text-4xl font-bold lg:tracking-tight mt-1 lg:leading-tight">
      Best Self Hosted {entry.data.title} Alternative
    </h1>
    <div class="mt-1">
      <span class="text-lg text-slate-500 italic">
        Master productivity by choosing the best-ever self-hosted solution!
      </span>
    </div>
    <div
      class="flex gap-2 mt-3 items-center justify-center text-sm flex-wrap md:flex-nowrap">
      <span class="text-slate-400">
        {entry.data.author}
      </span>
      <span class="text-slate-400">•</span>
      <time
        class="text-slate-400"
        datetime={entry.data.publishDate.toISOString()}>
        {entry.data.publishDate.toDateString()}
      </time>
      <span class="text-slate-400 hidden md:block">•</span>
      <div class="w-full md:w-auto flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-3">
        {
          entry.data.tags.map((tag) => (
            <span class="text-sm text-slate-500">#{tag}</span>
          ))
        }
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl">
    <Picture
      formats={["avif", "webp"]}
      src={entry.data.image.src}
      alt={entry.data.image.alt}
      width="1280"
      height="600"
      class="h-full w-full object-contain rounded-xl mt-6"
      transition:name={`post-img-${entry.slug}`}
    />
  </div>

  <div
    class="mx-auto prose mt-6 max-w-4xl prose-headings:mb-2 prose-headings:mt-8">
    <h2>Looking for the best Self-Hosted {entry.data.title} Alternative?</h2>
    <div
      class="mx-auto prose mt-6 max-w-4xl prose-headings:mb-2 prose-headings:mt-8">
      Finding a reliable project management tool can be challenging, especially
      with many available options. {entry.data.title} is a popular choice for many
      teams, but if you're looking for an self-hosted alternative, Worklenz is here
      to meet your needs
    </div>
    <!-- <div class="mx-auto prose mt-6 max-w-4xl prose-headings:mb-2 prose-headings:mt-8"> -->
    <h2>Worklenz - the best Self-Hosted {entry.data.title} Alternative</h2>
    <!-- </div> -->
    <div
      class="mx-auto prose mt-6 max-w-4xl prose-headings:mb-2 prose-headings:mt-8">
      <h3 class="text-xl font-bold">Why Consider Worklenz?</h3>
    </div>
    <div>
      <p>
        Worklenz stands out as an exceptional self-hosted project management
        tool that provides comprehensive features to help teams manage their
        projects effectively. Here’s why Worklenz might be the perfect fit for
        you.
      </p>
      <ul style="list-style-type: None;">
        <li>
          <h3>Comprehensive Features</h3>
          <p>
            Worklenz offers an extensive range of features designed to simplify
            project management. From project planning and task management to
            collaboration tools and time tracking, Worklenz has everything you
            need to keep your projects on track. The platform also provides
            detailed reporting on project status, team workload, and performance
            metrics, ensuring you have all the information you need at your
            fingertips.
          </p>

          <ol>
            <li>
              <b>Streamline Your Workflows with Task Management </b>
              <p>
                Worklenz provides an intuitive interface for assigning tasks,
                setting deadlines, and tracking progress. The task management
                dashboard simplifies complex projects into manageable steps.
              </p>
              <Picture
                formats={["avif", "webp"]}
                src="/images/Streamline-your-workflows-with-task-management.png"
                alt="the task assignment interface, showing a task list, assignees, and status progress bars."
                width="1280"
                height="600"
                class="h-full w-full object-contain rounded-xl mt-6 shadow-lg"
                transition:name={`post-img-${entry.slug}`}
              />
              <p>
                <b>Pro Tip:</b> Use color-coded labels in Worklenz to organize tasks
                by priority.
              </p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <b>Optimize Resource Allocation with Detailed Reporting </b>
              <p>
                Stay ahead with visually rich reports that offer insights into
                team performance, resource utilization, and project timelines.
                Customizable dashboards allow you to focus on what matters most
                to your project.
              </p>
              <Picture
                formats={["avif", "webp"]}
                src="/images/Optimize-resource-allocation-with-detailed-reporting.png"
                alt="performance analytics dashboard, featuring graphs, charts, and milestones"
                width="1280"
                height="600"
                class="h-full w-full object-contain rounded-xl mt-6 shadow-lg"
                transition:name={`post-img-${entry.slug}`}
              />
              <p
                class="flex gap-2 mt-3 items-center justify-center text-sm flex-wrap md:flex-nowrap">
                Easily export reports in various formats.
              </p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <b>Facilitate Teamwork with Seamless Collaboration Tools </b>
              <p>
                Effective collaboration is crucial for project success. With
                Worklenz, teams can share files, leave comments, and communicate
                directly within the platform—ensuring everyone stays on the same
                page.
              </p>
              <Picture
                formats={["avif", "webp"]}
                src="/images/Facilitate-teamwork-with-seamless-collaboration-tools.png"
                alt="performance analytics dashboard, featuring graphs, charts, and milestones"
                width="1280"
                height="600"
                class="h-full w-full object-contain rounded-xl mt-6 shadow-lg"
                transition:name={`post-img-${entry.slug}`}
              />
              <p
                class="flex gap-2 mt-3 items-center justify-center text-sm flex-wrap md:flex-nowrap">
                Encourage teamwork across remote and hybrid teams
              </p>
            </li>
          </ol>
        </li>
        <li>
          <h3>Seamless Collaboration</h3>
          <p>
            Effective collaboration is key to successful project management, and
            Worklenz excels in this area. With file sharing, comments, and
            communication tools, your team can collaborate effortlessly, no
            matter where they are.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <h3>Built for Scalability</h3>
          <p>
            Worklenz is designed to grow with your needs. Built using Angular
            for the front end and a custom TypeScript implementation of
            ExpressJS with PostgreSQL as the backend, it offers a scalable,
            reliable, and type-safe solution for project management.
          </p>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div
    class="mx-auto prose mt-6 max-w-4xl prose-headings:mb-2 prose-headings:mt-8">
    <h5 class="text-xl font-bold">
      It's Your Choice: Worklenz vs {entry.data.title}
    </h5>
  </div>
  <div
    class="mx-auto prose mt-6 max-w-3xl prose-headings:mb-2 prose-headings:mt-8">
    <table class="min-w-full bg-white border border-gray-200">
      <thead>
        <tr class="bg-gray-200 text-white">
          <th class="py-2 px-4 text-center border-b">Feature</th>
          <th class="py-2 px-4 text-center border-b">Worklenz</th>
          <th class="py-2 px-4 text-center border-b">{entry.data.title}</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr class="even:bg-gray-100">
          <td class="py-2 px-4 text-left border-b">Open-Source</td>
          <td class="py-2 px-4 text-center border-b"
            ><!-- Tailwind built-in classes -->
            <input
              type="checkbox"
              checked
              onclick="return false;"
              class="form-checkbox h-5 w-5 text-blue-600 checked:bg-blue-600 checked:border-blue-600"
            /></td
          >
          {
            entry.data.open_source_checked ? (
              <td class="py-2 px-4 text-center border-b">
                <input
                  type="checkbox"
                  checked
                  onclick="return false;"
                  class="center-checkbox form-checkbox h-5 w-5 text-blue-600"
                />
              </td>
            ) : (
              <td class="py-2 px-4 text-center border-b">
                <input
                  type="checkbox"
                  onclick="return false;"
                  class="center-checkbox form-checkbox h-5 w-5 text-blue-600"
                />
              </td>
            )
          }
        </tr>
        <tr class="even:bg-gray-100">
          <td class="py-2 px-4 text-left border-b">Self-Hosted</td>
          <td class="py-2 px-4 text-center border-b"
            ><input
              type="checkbox"
              checked
              onclick="return false;"
              class="center-checkbox form-checkbox h-5 w-5 text-blue-600"
            /></td
          >
          {
            entry.data.self_hosted_checked ? (
              <td class="py-2 px-4 text-center border-b">
                <input
                  type="checkbox"
                  checked
                  onclick="return false;"
                  class="center-checkbox form-checkbox h-5 w-5 text-blue-600"
                />
              </td>
            ) : (
              <td class="py-2 px-4 text-center border-b">
                <input
                  type="checkbox"
                  onclick="return false;"
                  class="center-checkbox form-checkbox h-5 w-5 text-blue-600"
                />
              </td>
            )
          }
        </tr>
        <tr class="even:bg-gray-100">
          <td class="py-2 px-4 text-left border-b">Cloud-based</td>
          <td class="py-2 px-4 text-center border-b"
            ><input
              type="checkbox"
              onclick="return false;"
              checked
              class="center-checkbox form-checkbox h-5 w-5 text-blue-600"
            /></td
          >
          {
            entry.data.cloud_based_checked ? (
              <td class="py-2 px-4 text-center border-b">
                <input
                  type="checkbox"
                  onclick="return false;"
                  checked
                  class="center-checkbox form-checkbox h-5 w-5 text-blue-600"
                />
              </td>
            ) : (
              <td class="py-2 px-4 text-center border-b">
                <input
                  type="checkbox"
                  onclick="return false;"
                  class="center-checkbox form-checkbox h-5 w-5 text-blue-600"
                />
              </td>
            )
          }
        </tr>
        <tr class="even:bg-gray-100">
          <td class="py-2 px-4 text-left border-b">Easy to use</td>
          <td class="py-2 px-4 text-center border-b"
            ><input
              type="checkbox"
              onclick="return false;"
              checked
              class="center-checkbox form-checkbox h-5 w-5 text-blue-600"
            /></td
          >
          {
            entry.data.easy_to_use_checked ? (
              <td class="py-2 px-4 text-center border-b">
                <input
                  type="checkbox"
                  onclick="return false;"
                  checked
                  class="center-checkbox form-checkbox h-5 w-5 text-blue-600"
                />
              </td>
            ) : (
              <td class="py-2 px-4 text-center border-b">
                <input
                  type="checkbox"
                  onclick="return false;"
                  class="center-checkbox form-checkbox h-5 w-5 text-blue-600"
                />
              </td>
            )
          }
        </tr>
        <tr class="even:bg-gray-100">
          <td class="py-2 px-4 text-left border-b">Data security</td>
          <td class="py-2 px-4 text-center border-b"
            ><input
              type="checkbox"
              onclick="return false;"
              checked
              class="form-checkbox h-5 w-5 text-blue-600"
            /></td
          >
          {
            entry.data.data_security_checked ? (
              <td class="py-2 px-4 text-center border-b">
                <input
                  type="checkbox"
                  onclick="return false;"
                  checked
                  class="form-checkbox h-5 w-5 text-blue-600"
                />
              </td>
            ) : (
              <td class="py-2 px-4 text-center border-b">
                <input
                  type="checkbox"
                  onclick="return false;"
                  class="form-checkbox h-5 w-5 text-blue-600"
                />
              </td>
            )
          }
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <!-- loging image -->
    <Picture
    formats={["avif", "webp"]}
    src="/images/Worklenz-login-page.png"
    alt="worklenz login page"
    width="1280"
    height="600"
    class="h-full w-full object-contain rounded-xl mt-6 shadow-lg"
    transition:name={`post-img-${entry.slug}`}
  />
  </div>
  <div
    class="mx-auto prose mt-6 max-w-4xl prose-headings:mb-2 prose-headings:mt-8">
    <h2>Top Reasons to Choose Worklenz</h2>
    <div>
      <p>
        Worklenz is an self-hosted project management tool that stands out for
        several reasons:
      </p>
  
      <ol>
        <li>Benefit from a customizable and flexible self-hosted platform.</li>
        <li>
          Gain a comprehensive view of your team’s resources and streamline their
          management with ease.
        </li>
        <li>Keep a close eye on task progress to ensure timely completion.</li>
        <li>
          Get a clear picture of your projects with detailed milestones and team
          contributions.
        </li>
        <li>
          Enjoy peace of mind knowing your data is protected with a scalable and
          type-safe backend.
        </li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div
    class="mx-auto prose mt-6 max-w-4xl prose-headings:mb-2 prose-headings:mt-8">
    <h2>Introduction to User Scenarios and Use Cases</h2>
    <div>
      <p>
        Choosing the right project management tool isn’t just about features, it’s
        about finding a solution that fits seamlessly into your team’s unique
        workflows and goals. Worklenz excels by addressing diverse teams' specific
        challenges, offering tailored solutions that {entry.data.title}
        and other tools often miss. Here are some real-world scenarios where Worklenz
        can be the superior choice.
      </p>
  
      <ol>
        <li>
          <b>Ideal for Teams Needing Data Security</b>
          <p>
            Worklenz’s self-hosted model ensures that your data remains within
            your control, making it the perfect choice for industries that handle
            sensitive information, such as healthcare, finance, or government
            projects.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <b>Flexible for Developers and Customization Enthusiasts</b>
          <p>
            As an open-source platform, Worklenz allows developers to tweak and
            enhance its features to meet unique business needs. Whether you want
            to integrate with other software or customize workflows, Worklenz
            provides the freedom to do so.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <b>Perfect for Growing Teams and Businesses</b>
          <p>
            With its scalable backend architecture, Worklenz grows alongside your
            organization, seamlessly handling increasing project demands and team
            sizes.
          </p>
        </li>
      </ol>
  
      <h2>Empower Your Projects with Worklenz</h2>
      <p>
        Switching to an open-source tool like Worklenz is more than just a cost-saving decision—it invests in flexibility, efficiency, and control. Worklenz offers the power to tailor workflows to your unique needs, ensuring your team operates at peak productivity. With robust features like advanced task management, collaboration tools, and detailed reporting, it simplifies complex projects and enhances team coordination. 
      </p>
      <p>
        Whether you're seeking a solution that prioritizes data security, scales with your business, or adapts to evolving requirements, Worklenz is a dependable alternative to {entry.data.title}.
      </p>
      <p>
        It combines the best of open-source freedom with enterprise-grade functionality, empowering you to meet your project goals with confidence and ease.
      </p>
      <p>
        Ready to take your project management to the next level? Make the switch to Worklenz today and experience the difference of a tool designed for teams that demand more.
      </p>
    </div>
    <Cta />
  </div>
</Container>
<hr class="mx-auto max-w-4xl mt-16 mb-16" />

<!-- Related Articles -->
<RelatedArticles entry={entry} />
<!-- Schema Articles -->
<JsonLd jsonLdData={jsonLdData} />
